<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="data-fields">3.15.1. Data fields for single item pages</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Since the release of Ceres 4.1, it is possible to insert item data fields with the inline editor. If you open the editor view of a content of the type <strong>item</strong> and open the inline editor of a widget, the navigational tree for item data fields will be displayed on the left side of the interface. The tree lists many useful item data fields that can be added to your texts. Uncollapse a section in the data field tree to show the corresponding data fields. Add a data field at the position of your cursor by clicking the data field in the navigation tree. If the data field is not specified for an item in the back end, no value is displayed in the online store.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding data fields to the item view:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Open a content for a single item view in the ShopBuilder editor.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Pencil</strong> icon (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-pencil  "></i></span>) on a widget to open the inline editor.
→ The navigation tree for item information is displayed on the left side.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand an area in the navigation by clicking on its title.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on an item data field to insert it at the position of the cursor in the inline editor.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
