<h2 id="design">4. Carry out design settings for plentyShop</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>When editing a content in the editor, you can click on the <strong>Design</strong>(<span class="icon "><i class="psicon-author"></i></span>) button.
This opens the design settings of ShopBuilder. In this menu, you carry out settings pertaining to the colour scheme and the fonts used in your online store.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="colours">4.1. Carry out colour settings in ShopBuilder</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can globally manage the colour scheme of all your pages in the ShopBuilder. The names of the 6 colour fields in the <strong>colour</strong> section are taken from the framework Bootstrap. You can define own colours for the 6 fields and access them via the drop-down list <strong>Appearance</strong> in most widgets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Select colours</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The content manager view of the ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on any content you created.<br>
→ The editor view opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Design</strong> button <span class="icon "><i class="psicon-author"></i></span>) in the tool bar.<br>
→ The <strong>Design</strong> menu opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings in the <strong>Colours</strong> section. Pay attention to the explanations given in <a href="#tabelle-farben-shop-builder">[tabelle-farben-shop-builder]</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
